[Patient] "I want to start exercising, but I don't have much money. What do you recommend?"
[Healthcare Educator] "You can try walking around your neighborhood or doing bodyweight exercises at home."
[Patient] "I'm worried about safety in my neighborhood. Is there a way to exercise indoors?"
[Healthcare Educator] "You can try online workout videos or use resistance bands for indoor exercises."
[Patient] "I don't have much time with work and family responsibilities. How can I fit in exercise?"
[Healthcare Educator] "You can break up exercise into shorter sessions throughout the day to make it more manageable."
[Patient] "I'm not sure if exercise will really help my heart failure. Can you explain why it's important?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Exercise can strengthen your heart and help manage your heart failure symptoms. Even small amounts can make a difference."